<div id="top-content">
  <div class="heading-with-actions top-heading">
    <h1>
      <span translate="no">epp</span> 
      <small class="app-vsn" translate="no">(stdlib v7.3)</small>

    </h1>

<a href="epp.md" title="Copy Markdown (hold Ctrl/Cmd and click it to open as Markdown)" class="copy-markdown icon-action" rel="help">
  <i class="ri-markdown-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  <span class="sr-only">Copy Markdown</span>
</a>



      <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/epp.erl#L22" title="View Source" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow">
        <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        <span class="sr-only">View Source</span>
      </a>

  </div>


    <section id="moduledoc">
<p>An Erlang code preprocessor.</p><p>The Erlang code preprocessor includes functions that are used by the <a href="../../../../lib/compiler/doc/html/compile.html"><code class="inline">compile</code></a>
module to preprocess macros and include files before the parsing takes place.</p><p>The Erlang source file <em id="encoding">encoding</em> is selected by a comment in one
of the first two lines of the source file. The first string matching the regular
expression <code class="inline">coding\s*[:=]\s*([-a-zA-Z0-9])+</code> selects the encoding. If the
matching string is not a valid encoding, it is ignored. The valid encodings are
<code class="inline">Latin-1</code> and <code class="inline">UTF-8</code>, where the case of the characters can be chosen freely.</p><p><em>Examples:</em></p><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="c1">%% coding: utf-8</span></code></pre><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="c1">%% For this file we have chosen encoding = Latin-1</span></code></pre><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="c1">%% -*- coding: latin-1 -*-</span></code></pre><h2 id="module-error-information" class="section-heading"><a href="#module-error-information" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">Error Information</span></h2><p><code class="inline">ErrorInfo</code> is the standard <code class="inline">ErrorInfo</code> structure that is returned from all I/O
modules. The format is as follows:</p><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="p" data-group-id="7708863948-1">{</span><span class="n">ErrorLine</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">Module</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">ErrorDescriptor</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7708863948-1">}</span></code></pre><p>A string describing the error is obtained with the following call:</p><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="n">Module</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">format_error</span><span class="p" data-group-id="1936819377-1">(</span><span class="n">ErrorDescriptor</span><span class="p" data-group-id="1936819377-1">)</span></code></pre><h3 id="module-see-also" class="section-heading"><a href="#module-see-also" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">See Also</span></h3><p><a href="erl_parse.html"><code class="inline">erl_parse</code></a></p>
    </section>

</div>

